-- Engevix Consortium Wins Brasilia Airport in Brazil Auction
-- B y   J o s e   S e r g i o   O s s e   a n d   T a i s   F u o c o
-- 2012-02-06T14:26:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/engevix-consortium-wins-brasilia-airport-in-brazil-auction.html
A consortium led by construction
company Engevix Engenharia SA won the license to operate the
airport in Brasilia after bidding 4.5 billion reais in an
auction today.  The consortium also includes Corporacion America, owner of
 Argentina ’s largest airport operator.  The minimum bid to manage for 25 years the airport in
 Brazil ’s capital was 582 million reais. The winners will have a
51 percent stake in the license while Brazil’s state-run airport
operator Infraero will retain a 49 percent stake in the
management of the airport.  Eleven groups participated in today’s auction, which also
leased the rights the Viracopos and Guarulhus airports near  Sao
Paulo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Sergio Osse in Sao Paulo at 
